-- compiler2 wall repro: VARIANT PAYLOAD ARITY ≤2 (sample-rung-walls.md).
-- The variant walker (compiler2/driver_claimidx.ev) has pay1/pay2
-- forms only — a 3-field payload spans past the 8-token lookahead
-- window. With the loud guard it halts Exit(8); before, the enum decl
-- was silently dropped. sample.ev's FloatLit(Int,Int,Int) /
-- EBinOp(Op,Expr,Expr) / ECall3 / ETernary variants hit this
-- (2026-06-10).
-- entry: main
-- expect: exit = 8 (compiler2 today; 0 once ≥3-field payloads land)
enum QA = QN(Int) | QB3(Int, Int, Int)
claim main
    t ∈ QA = QB3(1, 2, 3)
    ok ∈ Bool = (t matches QB3(_, _, _))
